HEADWORD: Speciosity
<hw>Spe`ci*os"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Speciocities</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Cf. LL.
<er>speciositas</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or state of
being specious; speciousness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Professions built so largely on <qex>speciosity</qex>, instead of
